(Bought on Humble Bundle Previously hence low steam play time)

Ladykiller in a Bind is the most mature writing games have ever done about sex and sexuality; it's also wonderfully immature, silly, and yet still smart and self-aware enough to fully pull off some incredibly consistent wit. You play as a perverted jerk pretending to be another kind of jerk so not to get spotted as a fake by a much of horny backstabbing teenagers while balancing being both S&M in 2 different relationships.

The writing is brilliantly funny (and wonderfully dirty);
The soundtrack is dynamic and a phenomenal addition to the game;
The conversation system is made of interjections and tangents that feel surprisingly naturalistic;
And it all somehow comes off being classy and clever despite the game insisting it's all smutty and stupid....
I'm not a visual novel fan at all but Christine Love has done it again and seduced me into actually reading something (the monster)!

So much more than just some erotica; it's smart, funny, and wholly unique for it!
